    <item>
      <title>ANTENNA</title>
      <link>https://darsa.info/project/antenna/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://darsa.info/project/antenna/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;ANTENNA&amp;rdquo; is a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.biodiversa.eu/2022/10/07/2022-2023-joint-call/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;biodiversa+&lt;/a&gt; project conducted by a European consortium (with leading scientists from Germany, Netherlands (Naturalis), Spain, Denmark, Ireland and Greece).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our overarching goal is to develop &lt;strong&gt;modern technologies, such as robotics, computer vision, and molecular methods&lt;/strong&gt; to complement traditional approaches, and ultimately help overcome key &lt;strong&gt;pollinator monitoring gaps&lt;/strong&gt;. The Role of DARSA in ANTENNA is to develop open-source, and readily usable camera-based and citizen-science methods to increase taxonomic and geographic coverage, speed, accuracy, content and efficiency of identification, and temporal resolution of pollinator monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
